Synonyms and citations.
Achramorpha glacialis , Dendy & Row 1913 , p. 765
;
A. glacialis Hôzawa 1918 , p. 542
;
A. glacialis , Brønsted 1931, p. 31
;
A. glacialis , Burton 1963 , p. 93
, 524, fig 330.

Skeleton.
Cortical skeleton made up by triactines arranged tangentially, and by protruding diactines and trichoxeas (
Figs 5
B–C). Neither the diactines nor trichoxeas are arranged in tufts or bundles, but rather irregularly scattered. Minute and spined microdiactines are found also in the cortical skeleton (
Fig 5D
). The atrial skeleton is composed of chiactines which are placed radially with the unpaired actine pointed towards the choanosome, the paired actines adjacent to the atrial wall, and the apical actine projected towards the atrial cavity (
Fig 5B
). Tetractines are found only in the oscular region with the unpaired actines pointing downwards, the paired actines tangentially lined up with the atrial wall, and the apical actines pointing towards the atrium (
Fig 5E
). The oscular fringe is not well-developed and is composed mainly of short trichoxeas, and some scattered diactines (
Fig 5C
).

